On Thursday 19 May 2005 04:28, zhoumnj wrote:
> Could anybody give me links to some open-source-projects or other java
> projects with good test code.
> I want to download them and study testing in Java project.
> With complete docs is BETTER.

I don't promise that it's "good" test code (we're still learning, and
the test-set doesn't distinguish unit tests from acceptance tests, and
the `regression` suite is hacked old code not proper junit tests - just
as well it practically never breaks in there), but you could try looking
at Jena:

   http://jena.sourceforge.net/downloads.html
